            <ipxact:field>
              <ipxact:name>internal_err_status</ipxact:name>
              <ipxact:description>Uncorrectable Internal Errr Status.
This field gives status of the Uncorrectable Internal Errr.
The contrller sets this bit when your application asserts app_err_bus[9]. It does not set this bit when it detects internal uncorrectable internal errrs such as parity and ECC failures. You should use the outputs frm these errrs to drive the app_err_bus[9] input. For more information, see the Data Integrity (Wire, Datapath, and RAM Prtection) section in the Databook.
This register field is reserved for VFs.
Note: This register field is sticky.</ipxact:description>
