            <ipxact:name>pf0_aer_cap_uncorr_err_mask_off</ipxact:name>
            <ipxact:description>The Uncorrectable Error Mask Register controls reporting of individual errors by the device Function to the PCI Express Root Complex through a PCI Express error Message.
A masked error (respective bit Set in the mask register) is not recorded or reported in the Header Log, TLP Prefix Log, or First Error Pointer, and is not reported to the PCI Express Root Complex by this Function.
There is a mask bit per error bit of the Uncorrectable Error Status register. Register fields for bits not implemented by the Function are hardwired to 0b.</ipxact:description>
