            <ipxact:name>pf0_aer_cap_uncorr_err_sev_off</ipxact:name>
            <ipxact:description>The Uncorrectable Error Severity Register controls whether an individual error is reported as a Non-fatal or Fatal error.
An error is reported as fatal when the corresponding error bit in the severity register is Set. If the bit is Clear, the corresponding error is considered non-fatal.</ipxact:description>
