          <ipxact:register>
            <ipxact:name>pf2_aer_cap_corr_err_mask_off</ipxact:name>
            <ipxact:description>The Correctable Error Mask Register controls reporting of individual correctable errors by this Function to the PCI Express Root Complex through a PCI Express error Message.
A masked error (respective bit Set in the mask register) is not reported to the PCI Express Root Complex by this Function.
There is a mask bit per error bit in the Correctable Error Status register. Register fields for bits not implemented by the Function are hardwired to 0b by the controller.</ipxact:description>
